    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthiyaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:1.2",
          "pli": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:1.3",
          "pli": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants!” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:1.4",
          "pli": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:1.5",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.1",
          "pli": "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, asurā deve abhiyaṃsu. ",
          "en": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, the demons marched against the gods. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṃ devaputtaṃ āmantesi: ",
          "en": "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the god Susīma, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.3",
          "pli": "‘ete, tāta susīma, asurā deve abhiyanti. ",
          "en": "‘Dear Susīma, the demons march against the gods! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.4",
          "pli": "Gaccha, tāta susīma, asure paccuyyāhī’ti. ",
          "en": "Go, and march against the demons!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.5",
          "pli": "‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, susīmo devaputto sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā pamādaṃ āpādesi. ",
          "en": "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Susīma. But he fell into negligence. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.6",
          "pli": "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṃ devaputtaṃ āmantesi … pe … ",
          "en": "For a second time … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.7",
          "pli": "dutiyampi pamādaṃ āpādesi. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.8",
          "pli": "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṃ devaputtaṃ āmantesi … pe … ",
          "en": "For a third time … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.9",
          "pli": "tatiyampi pamādaṃ āpādesi. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:2.10",
          "pli": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṃ devaputtaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
          "en": "Then Sakka addressed the god Susīma in verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:3.1",
          "pli": "‘Anuṭṭhahaṃ avāyāmaṃ, ",
          "en": "‘Susīma, go to that place "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:3.2",
          "pli": "sukhaṃ yatrādhigacchati; ",
          "en": "where you can achieve happiness "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:3.3",
          "pli": "Susīma tattha gacchāhi, ",
          "en": "without working for it or trying hard—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:3.4",
          "pli": "mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti. ",
          "en": "and take me with you!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:4.1",
          "pli": "‘Alasvassa anuṭṭhātā, ",
          "en": "‘That a lazy man who does no work, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:4.2",
          "pli": "na ca kiccāni kāraye; ",
          "en": "and doesn’t do his duty, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:4.3",
          "pli": "Sabbakāmasamiddhassa, ",
          "en": "should fulfill all his desires: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:4.4",
          "pli": "taṃ me sakka varaṃ disā’ti. ",
          "en": "Sakka, grant me this boon!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:5.1",
          "pli": "‘Yatthālaso anuṭṭhātā, ",
          "en": "‘Susīma, go to that place "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:5.2",
          "pli": "accantaṃ sukhamedhati; ",
          "en": "where a lazy man who does no work "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:5.3",
          "pli": "Susīma tattha gacchāhi, ",
          "en": "prospers in unending happiness—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:5.4",
          "pli": "mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti. ",
          "en": "and take me with you!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:6.1",
          "pli": "‘Akammunā devaseṭṭha, ",
          "en": "‘O Sakka, best of gods, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:6.2",
          "pli": "sakka vindemu yaṃ sukhaṃ; ",
          "en": "that we might find the happiness "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:6.3",
          "pli": "Asokaṃ anupāyāsaṃ, ",
          "en": "that’s sorrowless, unstressed: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:6.4",
          "pli": "taṃ me sakka varaṃ disā’ti. ",
          "en": "Sakka, grant me this boon!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:7.1",
          "pli": "‘Sace atthi akammena, ",
          "en": "‘If there exists anywhere a place "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:7.2",
          "pli": "koci kvaci na jīvati; ",
          "en": "where you can live happily without working, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:7.3",
          "pli": "Nibbānassa hi so maggo, ",
          "en": "that surely would be extinguishment’s path! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:7.4",
          "pli": "susīma tattha gacchāhi; ",
          "en": "Susīma, go to that place "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:7.5",
          "pli": "Mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti. ",
          "en": "and take me with you!’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:8.1",
          "pli": "So hi nāma, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sakaṃ puññaphalaṃ upajīvamāno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kārento uṭṭhānavīriyassa vaṇṇavādī bhavissati. ",
          "en": "So, mendicants, even Sakka, lord of gods—while living off of the fruit of his good and bad deeds, and ruling as sovereign lord over these gods of the Thirty-Three—will speak in praise of initiative and energy. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.2:8.2",
          "pli": "Idha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, sobhetha, yaṃ tumhe evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā uṭṭhaheyyātha ghaṭeyyātha vāyameyyātha appattassa pattiyā, anadhigatassa adhigamāya, asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti. ",
          "en": "But since you have gone forth in such a well explained teaching and training, it would be truly beautiful for you to try hard, strive, and make an effort to attain the unattained, achieve the unachieved, and realize the unrealized!”"
        }
      ],
